1. Used `browse_webpage` on `http://www.redscalar.com` to locate the latest application file.
2. Used `download_file_through_url` with `save_dir="/downloads"` to download the latest version from the site into `/downloads`.
3. Used `git_clone` to clone `emmajohnson/file_compression` into `/downloads` so I could modify the repo locally.
4. Used `copy_node` to move the downloaded application file (e.g., `/downloads/redscalar-latest.exe`) into the cloned repo root at `/downloads/file_compression/`.
5. Used `git_push` from `/downloads/file_compression` to upload the new file to the GitHub repository root.

These steps complete your request: the newest application file from www.redscalar.com is now in `/downloads` locally and also uploaded to the root directory of the `emmajohnson/file_compression` GitHub repository.
